    <div class="prob-grid r">
      <div class="prob-card"><div class="prob-n">01</div><div class="prob-ttl">Zero Real-Time Visibility</div><div class="prob-body">Operations teams managing 500+ purchase orders per month had no live view of anything. Every update required manual follow-up across email and WhatsApp. Decisions were made on stale data — or gut feel.</div></div>
      <div class="prob-card"><div class="prob-n">02</div><div class="prob-ttl">Seven Tools, One Job</div><div class="prob-body">Order management, freight booking, document sharing, supplier communication — all in separate tools. Context lost at every handoff. Nothing talked to anything else. Coordination happened in email threads 30+ replies deep.</div></div>
      <div class="prob-card"><div class="prob-n">03</div><div class="prob-ttl">No Accountability Layer</div><div class="prob-body">Without structured execution data, procurement teams had no defensible way to hold suppliers accountable. Every performance conversation devolved into dispute with no audit trail.</div></div>
